  "texts": [
    "DWT decomposes the image's features into multiple frequency components, which contributes to the classification accuracy.",
    "This allows models to extract high-level features and fine-grained details that are crucial for accurate classification.",
    "In this manner, these models can improve the capability of subtly distinguishing between various colorectal conditions and improve feature extraction procedures through DWT.",
    "In addition, the model exhibits exceptional generalisation performance in the testing region, with RV-22 + DWT and DEV-22 + DWT achieving testing accuracies of 90.9% and 91.5%, respectively.",
    "This minor deterioration in accuracy between the training and testing phases is quite common and indicates that the models have not overfitted to the training data but rather exhibit exceptional performance on unseen data."
